*Get Notified for Order Cancellation*


We have introduced a new notification sound configuration for *Order
Cancellation* events in the Rider App. Businesses can now configure a
dedicated alert tone that will play whenever an assigned order gets
cancelled from the rider.


This configuration is available within *Delivery Executive Settings =E2=86=
=92 App
Configurations =E2=86=92 Notifications*, positioned between *Order Allocati=
on*
and *General
Alerts* settings.


The rider will receive the following notification message on cancellation:
*=E2=80=9COops !! Order 123456789 was just cancelled=E2=80=9D*
This enhancement helps riders instantly differentiate cancellation alerts
from other operational notifications and respond with better awareness
during active deliveries.
Why We Built This?


Previously, order cancellation notifications followed the same general
alert experience, making it difficult for riders to quickly identify
cancellation-related events during active operations.
Since order cancellations often require immediate rider attention and
operational adjustments, introducing a dedicated configurable sound helps:

   -

   Improve rider awareness during live orders
   -

   Reduce missed cancellation notifications
   -

   Differentiate cancellations from other general alerts
   -

   Create a more intuitive rider notification experience

What=E2=80=99s New


A new configuration block has been introduced under:

*Delivery Executive Settings =E2=86=92 App Configurations =E2=86=92 Notific=
ations*

*=E2=86=92 Order Cancellations*

   -

   Businesses can select a dedicated notification tone for cancellation
   alerts
   -

   Sound preview/play functionality supported, similar to existing
   notification categories

*Rider Notification Message*
Whenever an assigned order is cancelled, the rider will receive:

*=E2=80=9COops !! Order 123456789 was just cancelled=E2=80=9D*
What This Means For You


For Operations Teams

   -

   Better communication of cancellation events to riders
   -

   Reduced confusion between allocation and cancellation alerts
   -

   Improved operational responsiveness during live delivery handling


For Riders

   -

   Easier identification of cancelled orders through distinct sounds
   -

   Faster reaction time for cancelled tasks
   -

   Improved app usability during high-order activity

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
